<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="R" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Reprieve1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Reprieve,</orth> subst. respite after condemnation: <cit><quote>three --s for you and your coach-fellow Nym,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.2.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. II, 2, 6</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>that in his r. he may be so fitted,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 2.4.39" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 4, 39</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>some pardon or r. for Claudio,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 4.2.74" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 74</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>wrought --s for him,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 4.2.74" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 74</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>out of r. and pardon,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 5.2.53" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. V, 2, 53</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>thy token of r.</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 5.3.249" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. V, 3, 249</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>